{{See|apollo}}
==English==
===Etymology===
Possibly from Greek [[απόλλυμι]] ("to destroy utterly"), or it may have entered Greek from an earlier, unknown language.

===Proper noun===
'''Apollo'''
{{wikipedia}}
# (''Greek, Roman mythology''): The son of [[Zeus]] and [[Leto]] (or [[Latona]] and [[Jupiter]]), and the twin brother of [[Artemis]] (or [[Diana]]). He was the god of light, music, prophecy, medicine, poetry, dance, manly beauty, and more.
# A very handsome young man.
# ''Space, U.S.'' A three-man spacecraft designed to travel to and land on the moon.
# A town in [[Pennsylvania]], [[USA]].

